<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>Electrical System Troubleshooting Guide - BE 200, CE 200, CE 300 Model - ELECTRONIC GAUGE CLUSTER - REMOVE
        AND INSTALL - EGC PANEL LAMPS AND GAUGE BACKLIGHTING LAMPS
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="0">
        <title>EGC PANEL LAMPS AND GAUGE BACKLIGHTING LAMPS</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk document="s08290_124.xml" xrefid="f08290554">EGC Exploded View</hotlnk>.
            <xref refid="f08290554"/>
        </para>
        <para>The EGC panel lamps are twist in lamps. To replace the lamps the failed lamp must be removed and replaced
            with a good lamp.
        </para>
        <seqlist>
            <item>
                <para>Remove the EGC from the instrument panel.</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Remove six screws holding the back of the EGC in place and remove the back cover.</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Locate the failed lamp and remove it by twisting it out of the circuit board.</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Replace the removed lamp with a good twist in indicator lamp.</para>
            </item>
        </seqlist>
    </svcproc>
